comment.narrative:
- The options to update Lebanon’s NDC are assessed, the mitigation options through derisking are enhanced, along with the adaptation options in the NDC, and a pilot scheme for private sector engagement is developed;
- Identify the common entry points for joint NDC and SDG implementation responses through policies, strategies and activities are identified; recommendations are generated; 
- A gender-climate analysis is conducted; standard operating procedures for mainstreaming gender in policies and climate instruments are developed, and capacities of stakeholders are built;
- The work of the NDC committee for mitigation is initiated;
- The legal components of the Paris Agreement to institutionalize its implementation is followed-up.

- Follow-up on updating Lebanons Nationally Determined Contribution (NDC) with national partners and donors (MoEW, FAO, MoA, MoF, LCEC, CDR, Green Plan, MoPWT, NCLW, WB, LRC, IFI-AUB, USJ, LAU, Bank Audi, Fransabank, UNE, EBRD, ClimaMED);
- Provided support to the mainstreaming of the NDC within various national entities (including support to the operationalisation of the NDC committee;
- Completed SDG/NDC synchronisation and gender-responsivness of NDC policies, inclduing over 10 workshops and meetings (with over 200 participants) with the national partners;
- Lead and provided technical and logistic support to: NDC Partnership kick-off meeting (Beirut-July) (around 50 experts), PATPA retreat (Lebanon- October) (around 50 International experts); 
- Provided strategic support to the MoE in preparation of its strategy with Strategy& (in climate change and air quality);
- Follow-up on Lebanons Low Emission Development Strategy;
- Participated and contributed to workshops and meetings: GCF (Korea), private companies to discuss PWC project; Pre-COP (Costa Rica), Climate Summit and Youth summit (NYC), COP25 (Madrid); Cartagena Dialogue (Costa Rica), CBIT (Rome), MR(Turkey)
- Resource Mobilization to MoE: CC activities with CLIMA-MED, Support provided in PIF prepration - GEF - Transport (USD 4 million); (USD 362K) - Technical assistance from CAEP, (USD 400K) - RBAS, (USD 860K) - GCF.

- A pilot scheme for private sector engagement within the NDC is developed;
- Lebanon submits its revised NDC to the UNFCCC;
- Lebanon ratifies the Paris Agreement;
- Lebanon presents its NDC Partnership Plan to partners for resource mobilization;
- Complete the preparation of Lebanons LEDS;
- Follow-up with National Council for Lebanese Women on adopting the gender Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs);
- Convene the national NDC committee at least once and continue work on mitigation workstream.

- Private sector engagement: 2 virtual exchanges, and 6 guidance documents and 1 climate plan (for Bank Audi) completed;
- Revision of NDC: 1) Completed the NDC and SDG synchronisation efforts and published 12 Integration Sheets ( Agriculture, Biodiversity, Electricity, Energy Efficiency, Forestry, Industry, Private and Public Transport, Renewable Energy, Solid Waste strategy, and Water); outputs delivered to PCM and secured the appointment of a focal point from PCM; 2) Gender Responsiveness of the NDC: in collaboration with NCLW, gender considerations in government policies completed, developed 2 Integration sheets on Gender Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs); 3) Finalized de-risking (1 report) ; NDC model under final review;
- Deposited the instrument of Ratification for Paris Agreement Jan 2020;
- NDC Partnership Support: in cooperation with the World Bank and IsDB, TORs for the CAEP support to design the LGIF launched; Partnership Plans (7 plans) under validation; initiated process for securing support under COVID-19 recovery to CDR (1 TOR prepared);
- GCF Advisory Service (delivered by Climate Analytics et al.): Organized and hosted LEDS, Climate Risk Profile, and Economic Profile inception mission with 20 representatives and experts from MoEW, LCEC, FAO, LRI, CAS, LARI, NOU, CEDRO, MoFinance, transport and energy - Feb 2020; provide national data and review draft outputs; UNDP Climate Promise: TORs launched, company recruited to undertake Climate-proofing Lebanon’s Economic and Investment Strategies , Kick-off meeting completed; Continue providing support to the South Centre project for the GCF Readiness ($850 000);
- Participated and contributed to (virtual) workshops, trainings, conferences and meetings related to Climate Change: Integration of Gender into MRV- Montenegro, GCF readiness projects, MRV on reducing GHG emissions, ESG, IRENA and renewable energy in NDC, lectures on CC to Balamand, ESA and USJ, usage of SCAN tool and SDGs, SDGs and nexus tool for Climate Promise, NDC Partnership Steering Committee Meeting - COVID-19 Impact, GIZ to prepare for GEF and CDR projects, Cartagena Dialogue, ICAT Webinar: Sustainable Development and Transformational Change Methodologies, CAEP Lebanon Coordination, A Green Recovery and the Financial System; Coordinate with GCF on 1 national readiness proposal (in favor of the MoEW), COP Chat young people powering Climate, Green Climate Fund Programming, Climate Change Dialogues; 
- Serve as NDC Partnership Steering Committee member/ICAT Advisory Committee member.
- Project completed all planned activities and targets and set to operationally closed by end of 2020.
